"source": "F3.M5",
"mcqId": "25491",
"q": "A company has a building with a carrying value of $350,000 that meets held for sale criteria. The fair value is $380,000, and costs to sell are $40,000. After two months, fair value drops to $320,000 with the same costs to sell. What amount should be recorded as the carrying value after subsequent measurement?",
"choices": [
"$350,000",
"$280,000",
"$340,000",
"$320,000"
],
"answer": 1,
