"mcqId": "12613",
"q": "The vacation policy for a company is as follows: 1–5 years of service = 6 annual vacation days; 6–10 years = 12 annual vacation days; 11+ years = 18 annual vacation days. Employee information: Employee A has 1 year of service, Employee B has 6 years, and Employee C has 12 years. The calendar-year company is closing its three-month period ended March 31. Each employee's gross pay is $100 per day, and no employee has taken vacation time as of March 31. What amount should be accrued for vacation pay for the three-month period ended March 31?",
