"q": "On January 1, Year 1, Day Corp. entered into a 10-year lease agreement with Ward, Inc. for industrial equipment. Annual lease payments of $10,000 are payable at the end of each year. Day knows that the lessor expects a 10% return on the lease. Day has a 12% incremental borrowing rate. The equipment is expected to have an estimated useful life of 10 years. In addition, a third party has guaranteed to pay Ward a residual value of $5,000 at the end of the lease. The present value of an ordinary annuity of $1 at: 12% for 10 years is 5.6502 10% for 10 years is 6.1446 The present value of $1 at: 12% for 10 years is 0.3220 10% for 10 years is 0.3855 In Day's January 1, Year 1 balance sheet, the principal amount of the lease obligation was:",
