"q": "Robbins Inc. leased a machine from Ready Leasing Co. The lease qualifies as a finance lease and requires 10 annual payments of $10,000 beginning immediately. The lease specifies an interest rate of 12% and a purchase option of $10,000 at the end of the tenth year; the machine's estimated value on that date is $20,000. Robbins intends to exercise this purchase option at the end of the lease. Robbins' incremental borrowing rate is 14%. The present value of an annuity due of 1 at: 12% for 10 years is 6.328 and 14% for 10 years is 5.946. The present value of 1 at: 12% for 10 years is 0.322 and 14% for 10 years is 0.270. What would the value of the lease liability be at the beginning of the lease term after the initial payment is made?",
