"q": "On December 31, Year 1, Neal Inc. leased machinery with a fair value of $105,000 from Frey Rentals Co. The agreement is a six-year noncancelable lease requiring annual payments of $20,000 beginning December 31, Year 1. The lease is appropriately accounted for by Neal as a finance lease. Neal's incremental borrowing rate is 11%. Neal knows the interest rate implicit in the lease payments is 10%. The present value of an annuity due of 1 for 6 years at 10% is 4.7908 The present value of an annuity due of 1 for 6 years at 11% is 4.6959 In its December 31, Year 1 balance sheet, Neal should report a lease liability of:",
