"q": "Steam Co. acquired equipment under a finance lease for six years. Minimum lease payments were $60,000 payable annually at year-end. The interest rate was 5% with an annuity factor for six years of 5.0757. The present value of the payments was equal to the fair market value of the equipment. What amount should Steam report as interest expense at the end of the first year of the lease?",
